actor.name: Truck
actor.description: This actor is responsible for transporting the crates from one place to another.

actor.name: Hoist
actor.description: This actor is responsible for arranging the crates at a place and loading then in to a truck.

useCase.name: Hoist unload a crate from a truck
useCase.description: The agent hoist unload a crate from a truck.

definition.invariants: - the truck, the crate and the hoist remain at the same place.

useCase.name: Hoist load a crate in a truck
useCase.description: The agent hoist loads a crate in a truck at a place.

definition.invariants: - the truck, the crate and the hoist remain at the same place.

useCase.name: Refuel truck
useCase.description: The agent truck is refueled at a fuel station.

definition.precondition: - the truck must have less fuel than its capacity; - the truck must be at the fuel station.
definition.postcondition: - the truck fuel level is incresead to its full capacity; - the fuel cost is increased.
definition.invariants: - the truck load remains the same; - the truck remains at the fuel station.

useCase.name: Drive from a place to another
useCase.description: The agent truck moves from an origin place to a destination place.

definition.precondition: - the truck must at the origin place; - the truck must have enough fuel, accordingly to the distance.
definition.postcondition: - the truck is at the destination place; - the truck has its fuel level decreased.
definition.invariants: - the truck load remains the same.

useCase.name: Lift a crate
useCase.description: The agent hoist lifts a crate from a surface (a pallet or another crate) at a place.

definition.invariants: - the hoist, the crate and the surface remain at the same place.

useCase.name: Drop a crate
useCase.description: The agent hoist drops a crate on a surface (a pallet or another crate) at a place.

definition.postcondition: - the crate is on the surface; - the hoist is available.
definition.invariants: - the hoist, the crate and the surface remain at the same place.

definition.precondition: - the hoist must have less fuel than its capacity.
definition.postcondition: - the fuel level is increased to the its full capacity; - the fuel cost is increased.

state.name: Crate being lifted
state.condition: c.at = null and c.clear = false and c.on = null and c.isIn = null

state.name: Crate in a Truck
state.condition: c.at = null and c.on = null and c.isIn = t

state.name: Crate on a Surface
state.condition: c.at = p and c.clear = true and c.on = s and c.isIn = null

state.name: Hoist lifting a crate at a place
state.condition: h.at = p and h.available = false and h.lifting = c

state.name: Hoist available at a place
state.condition: h.at = p and h.available = true and h.lifting = null

action.postcondition: h.fuelLevel = h.fuelCapacity and fuelCost = fuelCost + 2.30 * (h.fuelCapacity - h.fuelLevel)

state.name: Truck at a place with some fuel

action.postcondition: t.fuelLevel = t.fuelCapacity and fuelCost = fuelCost + fs.fuelPrice * (t.fuelCapacity - t.fuelLevel)

action.precondition: t.at = p1 and t.fuelLevel >= t.fuelBurn * distance(p1,p2)
action.postcondition: t.at = p2 and t.fuelLevel = t.fuelLevel - t.fuelBurn * distance(p1,p2)

action.precondition: t.at = p and t.loadLimit >= t.currentLoad + c.weight
